				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$I_{sQ}$$\end{document}IsQ (grey versus dotted and dashed dotted curves), i.e. the number of infected symptomatic individuals at the peak of the epidemic. As a result, countries with different proportions of symptomatic versus asymptomatic individuals (e.g. due to different age structure of the population or for other immunity reasons) might show different dynamics of the epidemic, although other conditions are similar. Introducing a reduction of the transmission due to quarantine by setting \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
